class Solution:
    def digitCount(self, num: str) -> bool:
        # Convert the string to a list of integers for easier manipulation
        num_list = [int(digit) for digit in num]

        # Check each index to see if the condition holds
        for i in range(len(num_list)):
            # Count occurrences of the digit i in the list
            if num_list.count(i) != num_list[i]:
                return False

        return True
```

This solution iterates through each index of the input string `num`, converts it to an integer list, and checks if the digit `i` appears `num[i]` times in the list. If any index fails this condition, it returns `False`. If all indices satisfy the condition, it returns `True`.
